{"author":"Iso Tester","data":{"alias":"cogent-strut-kid","description":"# S4 — Review-bot identity + event delivery + LLM-Review voter (the proven pipe)\n\n## Why\nClose the loop: on a new patchset the rebar MCP reviews the change and casts the\ndeterministic `LLM-Review` vote via REST. For d251 this proves the PIPE with a real\nvote; the full four-pass kernel reviewer + the real dogfood is b744-WS6, which plugs\ninto this same seam.\n\n## What\n- A dedicated Gerrit account for the bot in the built-in `Service Users` group (thread\n  isolation; excluded from the attention set except on a negative vote); its HTTP auth\n  token stored in SSM.\n- Event delivery: install the `webhooks` plugin (push patchset-created -> the MCP\n  endpoint) + the `events-log` plugin (replay/backfill so no event is permanently\n  missed). Because submit REQUIRES the vote, a missed event only DELAYS review (the\n  change stays unsubmittable) — it can never let an unreviewed change merge.\n- The MCP voter casts `LLM-Review` via `POST /a/changes/{id}/revisions/current/review`\n  with `robot_comments` (robot_id / robot_run_id / url) + the label; the deterministic\n  block/advisory outcome maps to the label value; `tag:autogenerated:rebar`, `notify:NONE`.\n\n## Scope\nIn: bot account + event plugins + the voter call using a minimal-but-real review path.\nOut: the full four-pass kernel reviewer + overlays (b744-WS6); replication (S5).\n\n## Files\n- `infra/gerrit/service-user.sh`, `infra/gerrit/webhooks.config`, the MCP voter wiring\n  under `infra/mcp/` (any thin webhook -> review -> vote shim)\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] On patchset-created, the bot casts an `LLM-Review` vote via REST with `robot_comments`\n      attached; a MAX vote makes the change submittable, a non-MAX/negative vote blocks it.\n- [ ] The bot account is in `Service Users` (SERVICE_USER tag; not added to the attention set\n      except on a negative vote); its auth token is sourced from SSM.\n- [ ] `events-log` is installed; a deliberately-dropped webhook is backfilled (no patchset\n      left permanently unreviewed), and a missed event NEVER yields a submittable-but-unreviewed\n      change (fail-closed).","id":"918c-589a-fc4a-4c52","parent_id":"d251-05e1-eb55-43b2","priority":2,"tags":["gerrit","mcp","llm"],"ticket_type":"story","title":"infra: S4 — Review-bot identity + event delivery + LLM-Review voter (proven pipe)"},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"CREATE","timestamp":1782685504064584001,"uuid":"f9759dae-8c42-4808-9b2f-5272a974119a"}